Monomorphization refers to the process of converting polymorphic code to monomorphic code (no type variables) through static analysis. Example: id : (A : Type) → A → A;
id _ a ≔ a; b : Bool;
b ≔ id Bool true; n : Nat;
n ≔ id Nat zero; Is translated into: id_Bool : Bool → Bool;
id_Bool a ≔ a; id_Nat : Nat → Nat;
id_Nat a ≔ a;

